 and colonialism. Shifting long-standing paradigms in the scholarship on modern Hebrew literature and culture, Zakai confronts the study of gender and Zionism with the critical sensibilities of contemporary global feminism. Read both critically and compassionately, the writings of women authors and activists not only reveal lives full of contradictions but also point to cultural structures that shape the politics of Israel/Palestine to this very day.Fictions of Gender rethinks Israeli feminism through the lens of contemporary feminism, intersectionality, and post-colonialism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminism in literature. 0aFeminismzIsrael. 0aHebrew literaturexWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aHebrew literature, Moderny19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aHebrew literature, Moderny20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aJewish women authorsy19th century. 0aJewish women authorsy20th century. 0aWomen in literature. 0aZionism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Feminist.2bisacsh  aAshkenazi.  aCare.  aColonialism.  aDebora Baron.  aDebora Ben Yehuda.  aEliezer Ben Yehuda.  aEthnicity.  aFeminism.  aHannah Thon.  aHebrew.  aHemda Ben Yehuda.  aIntersectionality.  aIsrael.  aJewish.  aLabor.  aLand.  aLiterature.  aMarginalization.  aMizrahi.  aMotherhood.  aNationalism.  aNehama Pohatchevsky.  aPalestine.  aPatriarchy.  aPhilantropy.  aPioneers.  aPower.  aRachel Bluwstein.  aRachel Katzanelson.  aSettler.  aShoshana Bluwstein.  aSisterhood.  aWhiteness.  aZionism.  afamily.  aideology.  anarrative.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542840uhttps: